26.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/166029426/image_166029426.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">aeduard</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><strong>All figures are in United States Dollars unless otherwise noted. G/T = grams per tonne (of gold or silver). GEOs = gold-equivalent ounces. SEOs = silver-equivalent ounces. AISC refers to all-in sustaining costs. LOMP = life of mine plan. TPD = tons per day. UG = underground.</strong></p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/166029426/image_166029426.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4745356-hecla-mining-back-on-the-sale-rack", "pub_date": "2024-12-19 19:16:36"}]}